15:40.320 --> 15:42.840
are connected to your fridge, but that wouldn't make them parts

15:42.840 --> 15:43.520
of the fridge.

15:45.920 --> 15:47.920
In fact, you can be a part of the fridge

15:47.920 --> 15:48.960
without being connected.

15:48.960 --> 15:51.400
There can be movable parts of the fridge.

15:51.400 --> 15:54.240
What makes a part most importantly is having a function.

15:54.240 --> 16:00.360
And Elsa Lyne sort of understood that in her way a bit.

16:00.360 --> 16:02.720
She didn't provide a definition of function.

16:02.720 --> 16:04.640
And we provided a definition of function

16:04.640 --> 16:05.920
which you can look at here.

16:05.920 --> 16:07.640
And it would be interesting if people

16:07.640 --> 16:11.320
have counter examples of entities with functions which

16:11.320 --> 16:14.160
do not satisfy this definition.

16:14.160 --> 16:18.600
Basically, what it says is that an object Y has a function

16:18.600 --> 16:21.880
means it has a disposition in virtue of the way

16:21.880 --> 16:23.880
it's built physically.

16:23.880 --> 16:26.880
And that entity came into existence

16:26.880 --> 16:28.680
through historical processes which

16:28.680 --> 16:34.000
selected for entities capable of realizing that disposition.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
And there are two ways that can happen.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.880
One is intentional design for artifacts

16:38.880 --> 16:41.160
like refrigerators and motor cars.

16:41.160 --> 16:44.320
And the other is evolutionary selection

16:44.320 --> 16:46.200
for biological entities.

16:46.200 --> 16:49.880
I don't know of any other way in which functional, sorry,

16:49.880 --> 16:52.600
in which entities with functions come into existence.

16:52.600 --> 16:55.520
So two of that kinds of things have functions, artifacts,

16:55.520 --> 16:57.760
and the component parts of artifacts,

16:57.760 --> 16:59.600
and parts of organisms.

16:59.600 --> 17:02.760
