17:02.760 --> 17:06.760
unless you believe in slavery or unless you

17:06.760 --> 17:10.760
follow Richard Dawkins and thinks that we are just

17:10.760 --> 17:14.120
the functional artifacts created by genes in order

17:14.120 --> 17:16.960
to propagate themselves through the universe.

17:16.960 --> 17:19.080
I don't accept them, either of those.

17:19.080 --> 17:21.480
So I can't think of any other reasons why organisms

17:21.480 --> 17:22.280
could be functions.

17:22.280 --> 17:27.840
Any organisms, whether bacteria or human beings.

17:27.840 --> 17:30.520
It could be that we manufacture bacteria

17:30.520 --> 17:32.680
and that we create artifact, and then they

17:32.680 --> 17:34.480
would have functions because we designed them

17:34.480 --> 17:37.840
for a certain purpose, to perform a certain function.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.400
But I can't think of any other ways

17:39.400 --> 17:41.800
in which biological entities can have functions other

17:41.800 --> 17:44.080
than being parts of organisms.

17:44.080 --> 17:45.120
Your heart has a function.

17:45.120 --> 17:47.160
Your kidney has a function.

17:47.160 --> 17:50.520
Your baby doesn't have a function because it's an organism.

17:50.520 --> 17:53.480
Therefore, your baby is not part of an organism

17:53.480 --> 17:57.680
because it doesn't satisfy that has a function relation.

17:57.680 --> 18:00.560
Now, in fact, what makes a part in the biological case

18:00.560 --> 18:02.040
is much more complicated.

18:02.080 --> 18:05.400
And that we could divide it into two questions, namely,

18:05.400 --> 18:08.440
the part question for small molecules.

18:08.440 --> 18:12.280
So banana molecules, when you've half digested a banana.

18:12.280 --> 18:15.400
Are the banana molecules parts of you or not?

18:15.400 --> 18:17.040
That's a very difficult kind of question.

