18:54.320 --> 18:55.840
They're parts.

18:55.840 --> 18:58.760
And all biologists accepts the blood cells

18:58.760 --> 19:00.280
as parts of your body.

19:00.280 --> 19:01.480
So what makes a part?

19:01.480 --> 19:03.480
Well, it can't be having a function either

19:03.480 --> 19:06.000
because prostheses have functions,

19:06.000 --> 19:08.280
but prostheses are not parts.

19:08.280 --> 19:12.000
Hair satisfies the criterion of having a function

19:12.000 --> 19:14.440
whose realization is necessary

19:14.440 --> 19:16.120
for the host's continued existence,

19:16.120 --> 19:18.520
or at least did originally satisfy that function

19:18.520 --> 19:22.040
before we had home heating and air conditioning and so forth.

19:22.040 --> 19:25.520
Microbiota are not parts.

19:25.520 --> 19:28.560
The embryo is not a part if the embryo is an organism.

19:28.560 --> 19:32.160
So could the embryo be something like an organ of the mother

19:32.160 --> 19:34.720
so that it could satisfy this criterion?

19:34.720 --> 19:36.880
Because an organ has a function.

19:36.880 --> 19:40.520
In fact, that's part of the definition of what an organ is.

19:40.520 --> 19:43.320
For Elsa Lyne to get her way,

19:43.320 --> 19:46.360
we have to find a way of recognizing

19:46.360 --> 19:48.760
that the embryo has a function

19:48.760 --> 19:51.360
and so that it can be an organ of the mother.

19:51.360 --> 19:53.520
It has to be a function which contributes

19:53.520 --> 19:56.640
to the mother's continued existence or something like that.

19:56.640 --> 19:59.360
In her talk today, Elsa Lyne told us

19:59.360 --> 20:03.240
