22:15.480 --> 22:19.720
which is equipped with an amnios or membrane.

22:19.720 --> 22:22.760
And the membrane is going to be a multi-layered membrane

22:22.760 --> 22:25.080
which enables certain kinds of exchange

22:25.080 --> 22:29.760
between the outside and the inside, protects the baby.

22:29.760 --> 22:32.840
And in mammals such as humans,

22:32.840 --> 22:35.120
these membranes include the amniotic sac

22:35.120 --> 22:36.280
that surrounds the fetus.

22:36.280 --> 22:39.480
So the amniotic sac is the niche

22:39.480 --> 22:41.280
and the fetus is the tenant.

22:42.360 --> 22:45.540
The chicken is the tenant, the egg,

22:45.540 --> 22:48.860
the interior of the egg is the niche.

22:48.860 --> 22:50.060
So this is where we are.

22:50.060 --> 22:54.060
We are amniota, these are the chordates.

22:55.180 --> 22:57.260
There are many, many other chordates,

22:57.260 --> 23:01.420
but we are here in the amniotic part of the chordates.

23:02.460 --> 23:05.820
And amniota include mammals,

23:05.820 --> 23:07.620
but they include all kinds of other stuff,

23:07.620 --> 23:12.020
including turtles and crocodiles and all birds.

23:12.020 --> 23:14.220
They lay eggs, remember, just like we do.

23:14.220 --> 23:18.300
So this is the anatomy of an amniotic egg.

